{
 "name": "RPlog_Jairen_Stops_a_Thief",
 "title": "Jairen Stops a Thief",
 "summary": "On a rainy night in Plaxton's SandBar on Caspar, the Marine pilot Tarlin Lathis, the cold Imperial-trained officer Joir, and the former TIE-pilot-turned-swoop-mechanic Azya share a wary, philosophical conversation over coffee, Joir baring an Imperial Royal Guard tattoo as he muses on discipline and chaos. The graceful, elf-eared swordsman Jairen arrives and quietly catches a pickpocket (Wil) in a wrist lock; when Wil's drunken friend Tegger draws a blaster on him at point-blank range, Jairen disassembles the gun with a lightning-fast stroke of his ornate sword, leaving Tegger to flee in terror straight into the arms of Tarlin's summoned Marines. The street musician Shenner, the bartender Ariani, and the self-important Dark Jedi Ozzle look on as the brief confrontation ends without bloodshed, Ariani rewarding Jairen's neat work with a drink on the house.",
